regfont
Temporarily register/unregister fonts under Microsoft® Windows® 2000 and above.
Copyright © 2010–2016  David Purton <dcpurton@marshwiggle.net>

regfont can be compiled using either the Gnu C Compiler or Microsoft Visual C++.


To compile using the Gnu C Compiler (under a UNIX-like shell), run:

    ./configure
    make
    make install

    If building from a clean checkout from GitHub first run ./autogen.sh

    Depends:
        - Gnu getopt (needs getopt_long)
        - Windows headers and libraries


To build under Microsoft Visual C++, after setting up your environment
appropriately, run:

    nmake /f Makefile.nmake

    Depends:
        - Microsoft Windows Platform SDK
